<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="281" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,893,1998]" pageId="14" pageNumber="281">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1829,1854]" pageId="14" pageNumber="281">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haran" authorityYear="2018" box="[342,574,1829,1854]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Smicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kenyanus">
<emphasis box="[342,574,1829,1854]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="281">Smicronyx kenyanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haran" authorityYear="2018" box="[840,987,1829,1854]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Smicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="namibicus">
<emphasis box="[840,987,1829,1854]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="281">S. namibicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its narrower prothorax and its less contrasting pattern of scales on the elytra (
<figureCitation box="[635,715,1865,1890]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1869,1891]" captionTargetBox="[223,1364,389,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[177,1399,389,1871]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Habitus of species of Smicronyx from tropical Africa (Part 1). A. Smicronyx bisignatus Hoffmann, holotype ♂. B. S. remaudierei Hoffmann, holotype ♂. C. S. adjamati, sp. n., holotype ♂. D. S. crassithorax sp. n., paratype ♀. E. S. zambianus sp. n. holotype ♂. F. S. syriacus Faust, specimen from Israel (♂). G. S. gossypii Marshall, holotype ♂. H. S. albosquamosus Wollaston, specimen from Israel (♂). I. S. pauperculus Wollaston, specimen from Tanzania (♂). J. S. rufus sp. n., holotype ♂. K. S. zonatus sp. n., holotype ♂. L. S. kenyanus sp. n., holotype ♂. Scale bars (A to L): 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2607090/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="281">Fig. 1J</figureCitation>
). It can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[1065,1186,1866,1889]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Smicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gossypii">
<emphasis box="[1065,1186,1866,1889]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="281">S. gossypii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Faust" authorityYear="1887" box="[1243,1365,1866,1889]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Smicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="syriacus">
<emphasis box="[1243,1365,1866,1889]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="281">S. syriacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its rostrum, which is longer and more downcurved in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[862,948,1901,1926]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1888,1910]" captionTargetBox="[170,1424,195,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[160,1430,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Head and prothorax in lateral view of species of Smicronyx from tropical Africa (Part 2). A. Smicronyx pauperculus Wollaston, specimen from Tanzania (♂). B. S. rufus sp. n., holotype ♂. C. S. zonatus sp. n., holotype ♂. D. S. kenyanus sp. n., holotype ♂. E. S. namibicus sp. n., holotype ♂. F. S. kiboanus Voss, paratype ♂. G. S. guineanus Voss, specimen from Senegal (♂). H. S. buchnerae sp. n., holotype ♂." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2607096/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="281">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
) than in the latter two species (
<figureCitation box="[1296,1371,1901,1926]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1905,1927]" captionTargetBox="[197,1395,245,1864]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[166,1433,199,1864]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Head and prothorax in lateral view of species of Smicronyx from tropical Africa (Part 1). A. Smicronyx bisignatus Hoffmann, holotype ♂. B. S. remaudierei Hoffmann, holotype ♂. C. S. adjamati, sp. n., holotype ♂. D. S. crassithorax sp. n., paratype ♀. E. S. zambianus sp. n. holotype ♂. F. S. syriacus Faust, specimen from Israel (♂). G. S. gossypii Marshall, holotype ♂. H. S. albosquamosus Wollaston, specimen from Israel (♂)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2607094/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="281">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
E–F). The penis is also very distinct, expanding regularly from base to apex (
<figureCitation box="[945,1025,1937,1962]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1825,1847]" captionTargetBox="[196,1389,189,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[165,1416,189,1815]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Penis of Smicronyx from tropical Africa, in dorsal (left) and lateral (right) view. A. Smicronyx bisignatus Hoffmann, holotype ♂. B. S. remaudierei Hoffmann, holotype ♂. C. S. adjamati, sp. n., holotype ♂. D. S. crassithorax sp. n., paratype ♀. E. S. zambianus sp. n. holotype ♂. F. S. syriacus Faust, specimen from Israel (♂). G. S. gossypii Marshall, holotype ♂. H. S. albosquamosus Wollaston, specimen from Israel (♂). I. S. pauperculus Wollaston, specimen from Tanzania (♂). J. S. rufus sp. n., holotype ♂. K. S. zonatus sp. n., holotype ♂. L. S. kenyanus sp. n., holotype ♂. M. S. namibicus sp. n., holotype ♂. N. S. kiboanus Voss, paratype ♂. O. S. guineanus Voss, specimen from Senegal (♂). P. S. buchnerae sp. n., holotype ♂. Scale bars (A to N): 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2607098/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="281">Fig. 5J</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,893,1998]" box="[199,1137,1973,1998]" pageId="14" pageNumber="281">
